Eragrostis tremula

    Authority   (Lam.) Hochst ex Steud.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5748

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass up to 75 cm high with widely spread panicle
   up to 15 cm long. USES Used as fodder for cattle, donkeys, goats and
   sheep. GROWING PERIOD Short-lived annual grass. The vegetative phase
   lasts 19-35 days and there is little vegetative growth after flowering
   starts. COMMON NAMES Bano, Bannu, Lehmleiche, Sarahol, Bibirua, Binnum.
   FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: E. lamarkii, E. serpula, Poa tremula.
   Bano can be found at elevations from 1000 to 1750 m and is common on
   sandy soils and in abandoned cultivation.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 431-433 [TEXT, RAIN, USE]
   White F 1983 pp 209 210 211 212
   IBPGR 1984 pp 1??

